namespace Forge.Api.Data.TrainingContent;

public class SearchTraining : TrainingContentBase
{
    public SearchTraining(AppDbContext db, Dictionary<string, int> slugMap) : base(db, slugMap) { }

    public override async Task SeedAsync()
    {
        // ── Overview (Article) ───────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Search Overview",
            Slug = "search-overview",
            Summary = "What global search does, entity types searched, full-text and RAG hybrid search, and keyboard shortcuts.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 3,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 1,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["search","global-search","navigation"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Global Search Overview\n\nGlobal search is always available from the header bar at the top of every page. It provides instant, cross-entity search across six core entity types, combining traditional full-text search with AI-powered RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) results when the AI module is enabled.\n\n### How It Works\n\nThe search input sits in the application header between the breadcrumb navigation and the action buttons. As you type, results appear in a dropdown overlay grouped by entity type. The system searches across six entity types simultaneously:\n\n- **Jobs** — matches on job number and title\n- **Customers** — matches on customer name and company name\n- **Parts** — matches on part number and description\n- **Leads** — matches on company name and contact name\n- **Assets** — matches on asset name and serial number\n- **Expenses** — matches on description and category\n\nSearch requires at least 2 characters before results appear. Results are debounced so the system waits for you to stop typing before querying — this keeps the interface responsive even on large datasets.\n\n### Desktop-Only Surface\n\nThe header search bar is a desktop feature. It is hidden on tablet and narrower (mobile) widths to keep the compact header usable — on those screens you navigate to the entity's own list page (Parts, Customers, Jobs, etc.) and use that page's filter instead. On a desktop browser the search bar is always present in the header (except during the new-hire onboarding flow, which has no header chrome).\n\n### Full-Text Search\n\nThe left column of the search overlay shows traditional full-text results. Each result displays an icon representing the entity type, the primary title (job number, part number, customer name, etc.), a subtitle with additional context, and a type label.\n\n**What happens when you click a result.** Clicking a result takes you to the entity's home route and opens that record's **detail dialog** right on top of it — it does not just drop you on a list page. Under the hood the search bar navigates to the entity's list route with a `?detail=type:id` query parameter (for example, clicking a part result goes to `/parts?detail=part:42`, which pops the Part detail dialog over the Parts list; a job goes to `/kanban?detail=job:1055`). Because the detail is encoded in the URL, the view is shareable and survives a refresh. Five of the six searchable types — Job, Part, Customer, Lead, and Asset — open their detail dialog this way. **Expenses are the exception:** an expense result simply lands you on the Expenses list page (there is no expense detail dialog), so you finish opening it from there.\n\n### AI-Powered RAG Results\n\nWhen the Ollama AI module is running, the search overlay expands to two columns. The right column shows AI results powered by RAG — Retrieval-Augmented Generation. This uses document embeddings stored in PostgreSQL via pgvector to find semantically related content, not just exact text matches.\n\nThe AI column shows:\n- A **generated answer** — a natural-language summary responding to your query\n- **Relevant document chunks** — pieces of indexed content that match your query, each with a relevance score percentage\n\nRAG results are especially useful for questions like 'what jobs involve aluminum machining' or 'which customer ordered the gear housing' — queries where the exact words might not appear in the record but the meaning is captured in indexed documents.\n\n### Keyboard Shortcuts\n\n- **Ctrl+K** — Focus the search input from anywhere in the application. This is the fastest way to start searching without reaching for the mouse. (Ctrl+K is the only keyboard shortcut wired up for search — there is no Escape handler.)\n- **Click away (blur)** — Click outside the search box and the results overlay closes on its own. The text you typed stays in the box.\n- **Click a result** — Open that entity's detail dialog (or, for an expense, its list page), clear the search input, and close the overlay\n\n### When to Use Global Search\n\n- When you need to quickly find a job by number or title\n- When looking up a customer or lead by name\n- When you know a part number but don't want to navigate to the Parts page first\n- When you have a vague query and want AI to help find relevant records\n- When jumping between different entity types frequently throughout the day","sections":[]}"""
        });

        // ── Walkthrough ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Search — Guided Tour",
            Slug = "search-walkthrough",
            Summary = "A guided tour of the global search overlay: search input, result columns, keyboard shortcuts, and AI-powered results.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Walkthrough,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 2,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["search","walkthrough"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"appRoute":"/dashboard","startButtonLabel":"Tour Search","steps":[{"element":".app-header__search","popover":{"title":"Global Search Bar","description":"This is the global search input, always available in the header. Type at least 2 characters to start searching across Jobs, Customers, Parts, Leads, Assets, and Expenses simultaneously. Results appear in a dropdown overlay below.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".app-header__search input","popover":{"title":"Search Input","description":"Type your query here. Search is debounced — results appear after you stop typing. The system searches across job numbers, customer names, part numbers, lead contacts, asset names/serial numbers, and expense descriptions. Press Ctrl+K from anywhere to jump directly to this input.","side":"bottom"},"advanceOn":{"event":"input","selector":".app-header__search input","predicate":"nonempty","hint":"Try it: type a search term in the box above to continue."}},{"element":".app-header__search kbd","popover":{"title":"Keyboard Shortcut Hint","description":"The Ctrl+K badge reminds you of the keyboard shortcut. Press Ctrl+K from any page to immediately focus the search input without using the mouse. Ctrl+K is the only keyboard shortcut for search; to dismiss the results overlay just click away from the box.","side":"bottom"},"advanceOn":{"event":"keydown","key":"k","ctrlKey":true,"hint":"Try it: press Ctrl+K (⌘K on Mac) to continue."}}]}"""
        });

        // ── Field Reference (QuickRef) ───────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Search Field Reference",
            Slug = "search-field-reference",
            Summary = "Complete reference for search input, entity type groups, result fields, keyboard shortcuts, and RAG integration.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.QuickRef,
            EstimatedMinutes = 3,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 3,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["search","reference"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"title":"Search Field Reference","groups":[{"heading":"Search Input","items":[{"label":"Location","value":"Header bar, between breadcrumb navigation and action buttons. Visible on all pages except onboarding."},{"label":"Availability","value":"Desktop-only. The search bar carries the hide-tablet class — it is hidden at tablet width and below. On tablet/mobile, use the target entity's own list page and its filter instead."},{"label":"Minimum characters","value":"2 characters required before search executes. Queries shorter than 2 characters return no results."},{"label":"Debounce","value":"Input is debounced — the system waits for you to stop typing before sending the query. This prevents excessive API calls during fast typing."},{"label":"Result limit","value":"Default 20 results, maximum 50. Results are distributed evenly across entity types (at least 3 per type)."},{"label":"Clear behavior","value":"Navigating to a result clears the search input and closes the results overlay. Clicking away (blur) closes the overlay but leaves the typed text in place."}]},{"heading":"Entity Types Searched","items":[{"label":"Job","value":"Searched fields: job_number, title. Icon: work. Click opens /kanban?detail=job:{id} — the job detail dialog over the board."},{"label":"Customer","value":"Searched fields: name, company_name. Icon: people. Click opens /customers?detail=customer:{id} — the customer detail dialog."},{"label":"Part","value":"Searched fields: part_number, description. Icon: inventory_2. Click opens /parts?detail=part:{id} — the part detail dialog over the Parts list."},{"label":"Lead","value":"Searched fields: company_name, contact_name. Icon: trending_up. Click opens /leads?detail=lead:{id} — the lead detail dialog."},{"label":"Asset","value":"Searched fields: name, serial_number. Icon: precision_manufacturing. Click opens /assets?detail=asset:{id} — the asset detail dialog."},{"label":"Expense","value":"Searched fields: description, category. Icon: receipt_long. Click navigates to /expenses (the list page). Expense is the one searchable type with no detail dialog, so no ?detail param is appended."}]},{"heading":"Result Fields","items":[{"label":"Icon","value":"Material icon representing the entity type (work, people, inventory_2, trending_up, precision_manufacturing, receipt_long)."},{"label":"Title","value":"Primary identifier: job number, customer name, part number, company name, asset name, or expense description."},{"label":"Subtitle","value":"Secondary context: job title, company name, part description, contact name, serial number, or expense category. May be null."},{"label":"Entity Type label","value":"Text badge showing the type (Job, Customer, Part, Lead, Asset, Expense) for quick identification."},{"label":"URL","value":"The entity's primary route returned by the server (/kanban, /customers, /parts, /leads, /assets, /expenses). On click, the search bar appends ?detail={type}:{id} to this route so the entity's detail dialog opens over its list — except Expense, which navigates to the bare /expenses route (no detail dialog exists)."}]},{"heading":"Keyboard Shortcuts","items":[{"label":"Ctrl+K","value":"Focus the search input from anywhere in the application. Works on all pages. This is the only keyboard shortcut wired up for search — there is no Escape handler."},{"label":"Click away (blur)","value":"Clicking outside the search box closes the results overlay (after a short delay so a result click still registers). It does NOT clear the text you typed — the query stays in the box."},{"label":"Click result","value":"Navigate to the selected entity and open its detail dialog via ?detail=type:id (expenses go to the /expenses list page instead), then close the overlay. The search input is cleared automatically."}]},{"heading":"RAG / AI Results (when AI module is active)","items":[{"label":"Two-column layout","value":"When AI is available, the search overlay expands to show two columns: full-text results on the left, AI results on the right."},{"label":"Generated answer","value":"A natural-language summary answering your query, displayed with a lightbulb icon. Generated by the Ollama AI model using RAG context."},{"label":"Document chunks","value":"Relevant text chunks from indexed documents. Each shows the chunk text, the source field it was extracted from, the entity type, and a relevance score as a percentage."},{"label":"Relevance score","value":"Percentage indicating how closely the document chunk matches your query semantically. Higher scores mean stronger relevance."},{"label":"Thinking indicator","value":"A spinning icon with 'Thinking...' text appears while the AI model processes your query. AI results may take slightly longer than full-text results."},{"label":"Fallback","value":"If the AI module is not running or unavailable, the search overlay shows only the single full-text results column. No error is displayed — AI simply degrades gracefully."}]},{"heading":"Search API","items":[{"label":"Endpoint","value":"GET /api/v1/search?q={term}&limit={limit}. Requires authentication. Returns a flat list of SearchResult objects."},{"label":"Query parameter: q","value":"The search term. Must be at least 2 characters. Searches using ILIKE pattern matching (case-insensitive contains)."},{"label":"Query parameter: limit","value":"Maximum number of results to return. Default: 20, maximum: 50. Clamped server-side."},{"label":"Response shape","value":"Array of SearchResult: { entityType, entityId, title, subtitle, icon, url }. Results from all 6 entity types are combined in a single list."},{"label":"UNION ALL query","value":"Server executes a single SQL query with UNION ALL across 6 entity tables. Each entity sub-query has its own LIMIT (total limit / 4, minimum 3 per entity type)."},{"label":"Soft-delete filter","value":"All searches exclude soft-deleted records (deleted_at IS NULL). Job searches also exclude archived jobs (is_archived = false)."}]}]}"""
        });

        // ── Knowledge Check (Quiz) ───────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Search Knowledge Check",
            Slug = "search-quiz",
            Summary = "Test your knowledge of global search: keyboard shortcuts, entity types, result layout, and RAG integration.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Quiz,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 4,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["search","quiz"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"passingScore":80,"questionsPerQuiz":8,"shuffleOptions":true,"showExplanationsAfterSubmit":true,"questions":[{"id":"sr1","text":"You need to quickly find a job but you're currently on the Expenses page. What is the fastest way to start searching?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Navigate to the Kanban board first, then use the board's search filter"},{"id":"b","text":"Press Ctrl+K to focus the global search input in the header, then type the job number","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Go to Reports and run a Job Lookup report"},{"id":"d","text":"Open the sidebar and click the Search menu item"}],"explanation":"Ctrl+K focuses the global search input from any page. You don't need to navigate anywhere first — just press Ctrl+K and start typing. The search bar is always available in the header."},{"id":"sr2","text":"How many entity types does global search query simultaneously?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"3 — Jobs, Parts, and Customers"},{"id":"b","text":"4 — Jobs, Customers, Parts, and Leads"},{"id":"c","text":"6 — Jobs, Customers, Parts, Leads, Assets, and Expenses","isCorrect":true},{"id":"d","text":"All entity types in the database"}],"explanation":"Global search queries 6 entity types in a single UNION ALL query: Jobs, Customers, Parts, Leads, Assets, and Expenses. Each type has its own searchable fields and icon."},{"id":"sr3","text":"You type a single letter 'A' into the search bar. What happens?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Results appear showing all entities starting with A"},{"id":"b","text":"Nothing — search requires at least 2 characters before executing","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"An error message appears asking you to type more"},{"id":"d","text":"The AI module generates suggestions based on the letter"}],"explanation":"Global search requires a minimum of 2 characters before it queries the server. Queries shorter than 2 characters return no results. This prevents overly broad searches that would return too many results."},{"id":"sr4","text":"What information does each search result display?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Only the entity name and a link"},{"id":"b","text":"An icon for the entity type, primary title, subtitle with context, and a type label","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"A thumbnail image, full description, and creation date"},{"id":"d","text":"The entity ID, database table name, and last modified timestamp"}],"explanation":"Each search result shows four elements: an icon identifying the entity type (work, people, inventory_2, etc.), the primary title (job number, customer name, etc.), a subtitle with additional context, and a type label (Job, Customer, Part, etc.)."},{"id":"sr5","text":"The search overlay shows two columns instead of one. What does this mean?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"There are too many results to fit in one column"},{"id":"b","text":"The AI module is active, showing full-text results on the left and RAG-powered AI results on the right","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"You are searching across two different databases"},{"id":"d","text":"The screen is wide enough for a two-column layout"}],"explanation":"When the Ollama AI module is running, the search overlay expands to two columns. The left column shows traditional full-text search results, while the right column shows AI-powered RAG results including a generated answer and semantically relevant document chunks."},{"id":"sr6","text":"A RAG search result shows a relevance score of 87%. What does this score represent?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The percentage of keywords from your query found in the document"},{"id":"b","text":"How semantically similar the document chunk is to your search query, based on vector embeddings","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The confidence that the document is not a duplicate"},{"id":"d","text":"The percentage of the document that has been indexed"}],"explanation":"The relevance score is a semantic similarity percentage based on vector embeddings (pgvector). It measures how closely the meaning of the document chunk matches your query, not just keyword overlap. Higher scores indicate stronger semantic relevance."},{"id":"sr7","text":"You search for 'aluminum housing' but no exact matches exist in job titles or part numbers. How can global search still help?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It cannot — global search only matches exact text in specific fields"},{"id":"b","text":"The AI/RAG column can find semantically related records even without exact keyword matches, returning relevant document chunks and a generated answer","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"It automatically switches to a fuzzy search mode"},{"id":"d","text":"It searches the full text of all uploaded PDF documents"}],"explanation":"RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) uses vector embeddings to find semantically related content. Even if 'aluminum housing' doesn't appear verbatim in any record, the AI column can find documents that discuss aluminum machining or housing components and present relevant chunks with a generated answer."},{"id":"sr8","text":"You click a Part result in the search overlay. What happens next?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The app navigates to /parts?detail=part:{id}, opening the Part detail dialog over the Parts list; the input clears and the overlay closes","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"The application navigates to the bare /parts list page with nothing selected"},{"id":"c","text":"The part information is copied to your clipboard"},{"id":"d","text":"A new browser tab opens with the part details"}],"explanation":"Clicking a result doesn't just drop you on a list page — it appends ?detail=type:id to the entity's route (here /parts?detail=part:{id}), which opens that record's detail dialog right over its list. Because the detail is in the URL it is shareable and survives a refresh. Job/Customer/Lead/Asset behave the same way; an Expense result is the only exception (no detail dialog — it lands on the /expenses list)."}]}"""
        });

        // ── Advanced Reference (Reference) ───────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Global Search — Advanced Reference",
            Slug = "search-reference",
            Summary = "Edge-case reference for global search: result distribution/limits, ILIKE matching, dual debounce, RAG routing/scoring, Documentation filtering, and desktop-only visibility.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Reference,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 90,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["search","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Result Distribution, Limits & ILIKE Matching\n\nThe full-text side is a single raw SQL `UNION ALL` over six tables (`jobs`, `customers`, `parts`, `leads`, `assets`, `expenses`), run by `SearchRepository.SearchAsync`.\n\n- **Per-entity fairness.** Each sub-query gets its own cap: `perEntity = Math.Max(limit / 4, 3)`. With the default `limit` of 20 that is 5 rows per entity; the floor of 3 guarantees a thin entity type is never fully crowded out by a noisy one. Each sub-query is `ORDER BY updated_at DESC LIMIT @per`, so the most recently touched records win within a type.\n- **Overall cap.** After the union, the handler returns `results.Take(limit)` — the union can surface up to `6 × perEntity` rows, but only the first `limit` reach the client. Distribution is therefore biased toward the entity order in the SQL (Job, Customer, Part, Lead, Asset, Expense) when the cap clips the tail.\n- **`limit` clamping.** `GET /api/v1/search?q={term}&limit={limit}` defaults `limit` to 20 and clamps it server-side with `Math.Min(limit, 50)` — 50 is the hard ceiling. `GlobalSearchQuery` also defaults to 20 if omitted.\n- **Minimum query length.** The controller returns an empty list when `q` is null/whitespace or `q.Length < 2`. The query is `q.Trim()`-ed before matching.\n- **ILIKE matching.** Matching is `column ILIKE @pattern` with `@pattern = %{term}%` — a case-insensitive substring (contains) match, not full-text-search ranking and not prefix-only. Each entity matches two columns (e.g. Job = `job_number` OR `title`; Part = `part_number` OR `description`).\n- **Soft-delete & archive filters.** Every sub-query filters `deleted_at IS NULL`; the Job sub-query additionally requires `is_archived = false`, so archived jobs never appear in global search.\n\n## Dual Debounce (Full-Text vs RAG)\n\nThe header search input drives two independent `valueChanges` pipelines with different debounce windows, so the fast full-text column and the slower AI column update on their own cadence:\n\n- **Full-text pipeline:** `debounceTime(300)` → `distinctUntilChanged()` → `filter(length >= 2)` → `searchService.search(term)`. ~300 ms after you stop typing the left column refreshes.\n- **RAG pipeline:** `debounceTime(600)` → `distinctUntilChanged()` → `filter(length >= 2)` → `filter(aiService.available())` → `aiService.ragSearch(term, undefined, true)`. The longer 600 ms window plus the availability gate means the AI request only fires when the AI module is up and only after a longer pause — avoiding an expensive embedding round-trip on every keystroke.\n- **Clear pipeline:** a third subscription on `filter(length < 2)` resets `aiSuggestions`, `ragResults`, `ragAnswer`, and `aiLoading` so clearing the box wipes stale AI state.\n- **Shortcuts:** `Ctrl+K` / `⌘K` focuses `.search-input` (global `document:keydown`); blur hides results after a 200 ms delay so a result click registers first.\n\n## RAG Routing, Scoring & Documentation Filtering\n\nThe AI column is backed by `RagSearchCommand` (`Query`, `EntityTypeFilter`, `IncludeAnswer`) handled by `RagSearchHandler`.\n\n- **Routing.** The query string is embedded via `aiService.GetEmbeddingAsync`; if the embedding service throws (container down), the handler logs a warning and returns `EmptyResponse` — graceful degradation, no error surfaced. The embedding vector is passed to `embeddingRepo.SearchSimilarAsync(queryVector, 10, EntityTypeFilter, ct)`, which pgvector-orders the `DocumentEmbedding` index by ascending cosine distance and returns the top 10.\n- **Scoring is positional, not raw cosine.** The handler does NOT expose the true distance. It approximates a 0–1 relevance score from rank order: `score = 1.0 - (index * 0.05)`, clamped with `Math.Max(0, score)`. So result #1 ≈ 1.00 (100%), #2 ≈ 0.95, and rank 20+ floors at 0. Treat the percentage as a relative ordering cue, not a calibrated similarity.\n- **Generated answer.** Only when `IncludeAnswer` is true AND there is at least one chunk does the handler build a prompt from the top 5 chunks and call `aiService.GenerateTextAsync`. A generation failure logs a warning and leaves the answer null while still returning the chunk list. The header always calls `ragSearch(term, undefined, true)`, so an answer is requested whenever AI is available.\n- **`EntityTypeFilter`.** The header passes `undefined` (no server-side type filter) — all indexed entity types are eligible. The parameter exists for callers that want to scope RAG to one type; validation caps it at 50 chars and `Query` at 2000.\n- **Documentation filtering is client-side.** Indexed content includes an internal `Documentation` entity type that is not useful to end users. The header drops it after the response: `response.results.filter(r => r.entityType !== 'Documentation')`. The server still returns Documentation chunks; only the UI hides them.\n- **Each RAG result** carries `entityType`, `entityId`, `chunkText`, `sourceField` (the indexed field the chunk came from), and the positional `score`.\n\n## Desktop-Only Visibility\n\nThe header search bar carries the `hide-tablet` CSS class (`.app-header__search hide-tablet`), the same utility class used by the breadcrumb and header separator. It is hidden at tablet width and below, so global search is a desktop-only affordance.\n\n- On tablet/mobile there is no fallback search field in the header — navigate to the target entity's own list page (Parts, Customers, Jobs, etc.) and use that page's filter instead.\n- The bar is also absent during the new-hire onboarding flow, which renders without header chrome.\n- Because visibility is purely a CSS breakpoint, the `Ctrl+K` shortcut and the `/api/v1/search` endpoint still exist on narrow viewports — only the visible input is suppressed.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        Log.Information("Seeded Search training modules");
    }
}
